The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for optimizing mobile networks, which involves complex real-world problems with incomplete and imperfect information, huge state/action space, and multi-agent interactions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves coordination of multi-agents to maximize global reward and minimize potential negative impact, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of mobile networks, which involves information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
